hxblas_linux.c is a native FFI shim (not a hexa compilation target).
It exists so Linux x86_64 hosts (e.g. H100 pod) can link against
libhxblas.so with the same ABI that Mac uses for libhxblas.dylib —
symbol-for-symbol identical, so hexa @link("libhxblas") code is
platform-agnostic at the source level.

Do not transpile, do not include in the stage0 pipeline. Compiled
only by scripts/build_hxblas_linux.hexa.
